2,187 Shares in Newell Brands Inc. (NWL) Acquired by Harfst & Associates Inc.


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments




Harfst & Associates Inc. purchased a new stake in  Newell Brands Inc. (NYSE:NWL) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  purchased 2,187 shares of the company’s stock, valued at approximately $103,000. 
Several other institutional investors have also recently modified their holdings of NWL. Israel Discount Bank of New York bought a new position in shares of  Newell Brands during the first quarter valued at about $112,000.  Parallel Advisors LLC boosted its position in shares of  Newell Brands by 23.0% in the first quarter. Parallel Advisors LLC now owns 2,906 shares of the company’s stock valued at $132,000 after buying an additional 544 shares in the last quarter.  Duncker Streett & Co. Inc. bought a new position in shares of  Newell Brands during the first quarter valued at about $186,000.  Global X Management Co. LLC boosted its stake in shares of  Newell Brands by 29.3% in the first quarter. Global X Management Co. LLC now owns 4,146 shares of the company’s stock worth $196,000 after buying an additional 940 shares during the period.  Finally, Zions Bancorporation boosted its stake in shares of  Newell Brands by 1.6% in the fourth quarter. Zions Bancorporation now owns 4,426 shares of the company’s stock worth $198,000 after buying an additional 68 shares during the period. 94.23% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Newell Brands Inc. alerts:



Newell Brands Inc. (NYSE NWL) traded down 0.38% on Friday, reaching $52.90. 2,587,656 shares of the company’s stock were exchanged. The stock has a market cap of $25.56 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 22.45 and a beta of 1.17. Newell Brands Inc. has a one year low of $43.43 and a one year high of $55.45. The firm has a 50 day moving average of $53.40 and a 200-day moving average of $49.49. 





Newell Brands (NYSE:NWL) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Monday, May 8th. The company reported $0.34 EPS for the quarter, topping the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.29 by $0.05. The firm had revenue of $3.27 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.23 billion. Newell Brands had a return on equity of 11.07% and a net margin of 7.40%. The firm’s revenue was up 148.4% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the prior year, the business earned $0.40 EPS.  Equities research analysts forecast that  Newell Brands Inc. will post $3.12 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
