Harfst and Associates, Inc. - eBook LibraryHarfst and Associates, Inc.An Independent Water Management CompanyP.O. Box 276Crystal Lake, IL 60039ph: (815) 861-9082fax: (815) 477-7824wfh@mc.netHome About the Consultant Capabilities Recent Articles Workshops and Seminars eBook Library Contact Us eBook LibraryThe following eBooks are intended to provide you with practical information on a variety of water topics.  These are available in PDF format for easy viewing on your computer screen using the Adobe Reader. If you would like a copy of one of my eBooks, please go to the Contact Us page and send a request by providing your name, company, email address (very important), and indicate the title of the eBook in the Question/comment box. We'll send the eBook to you by return email.Non-chemical water treatmentNon-chemical methods for conditioning water for use in cooling towers and boilers have been promoted for over 100 years.  Because of the growing interest in conserving water, reducing discharge of chemicals into the environment, limiting exposure of workers to hazardous chemicals, and the ever-present need to save energy, engineers are once again reviewing the benefits of non-chemical water treatment devices.  This eBook describes the common types of equipment marketed for this purpose including magnetic, electrostatic, ultrasonic, galvanic, electro-chemical, electro-deposition, membrane separtion, ozone, and ultraviolet.Swimming Pool Chemistry: a basic approach to pool maintenanceIf you own one of the 10 million private or 360 thousand public swimming pools in the US, you are familiar with the need to sample and test the water for pH and chlorine levels.  Based on the test results, various chemicals are added to bring the water into balance.  Swimming pool chemicals are marketed by a variety of suppliers under many brand names.  These products all work well when used according to the label directions.  What is not commonly known, however, is that brand name swimming pool products are chemically identical to common household products that are found in your kitchen cabinets or amongst your cleaning supplies.  This eBook teaches you how to keep your pool water clear, clean and sanitary by using simple environmentally-friendly household products like baking soda, chlorine bleach, washing soda, acid and salt instead of the more-expensive brand name pool chemicals sold in the retail shops.If you use water, we're good people to know...My goal is to provide you with unbiased information on water treatment technology.  Please check back with us as our eBook library grows.   Have Questions?If you have any questions or require more details on any of the topics covered in these eBooks, please feel free to contact me. We welcome your questions and queries. Please see our Contact Us page for complete contact information.   Copyright Harfst and Associates, inc. All rights reserved. Web Hosting by Yahoo! P.O. Box 276Crystal Lake, IL 60039ph: (815) 861-9082fax: (815) 477-7824wfh@mc.net  
