Harfst and Associates, Inc. - Workshops and SeminarsHarfst and Associates, Inc.An Independent Water Management CompanyP.O. Box 276Crystal Lake, IL 60039ph: (815) 861-9082fax: (815) 477-7824wfh@mc.netHome About the Consultant Capabilities Recent Articles Workshops and Seminars eBook Library Contact Us Workshops and SeminarsAn important part of my consulting work includes providing education for plant operators and supervisors.  These workshops are designed for 2 to 4 hours sessions in a classroom setting.  This allows flexibility in scheduling these workshops to fit into a busy plant schedule.Fundamentals of industrial water treatmentThis workshop reviews the problems water can cause such as scale deposition, corrosion, and microbiological considerations.  It includes a general introduction to water chemistry, water testing methods and water quality control methods.  2 hoursfiltrationTopics include activated carbon filtration, iron and manganese removal, gravity and pressure filters along with a general comparison of the various filter media used to condition water.  2 hoursIon exchange technologyThis workshop covers the basics of ion exchange technology.  Discussions include how ion exchange works, ion exchang calculations, operation and maintenance of ion exchange systems and troubleshooting tips.  This information is relevant to owners and operators of softeners, dealkalizers and demineralizers.  2 to 3 hoursReverse osmosisThis 4-hour workshop discusses the practical aspects of operation and maintenance of reverse osmosis systems.  This includes how reverse osmosis works, pretreatment requirements, performance monitoring and chemical cleaning.  Practical troubleshooting tips are also offered.  Excellent information for novice or experienced plant personnel.  4 hoursCooling towers and closed cooling loopsThis program presents the water treatment requirements for open and closed cooling water systems.  Subjects include cooling towers and cooling water system design, water chemistry, system calculations and operating parameters.  Various chemical treatment options are discussed including scale and corrosion inhibitors along with microbiological control agents.  4 hourssteam boilers and condensate systemsThis seminar addresses the water treatment requirements for steam and hot water systems.  Topics include pretreatment of boiler feedwater, scale inhibition, sludge conditioning, corrosion control, boiler calculations and water quality guidelines.  A review of recent developments in boiler water chemistry is included.  4 hoursIf you use water, we're good people to know...My goal is to work with everyone involved with your water management program to help them better understand the technology that they work with every day.Contact us today for more details  What Can You Expect?Sending employess off-site for training is expensive.  And with current budget cutbacks, travel and training expenses are often the first to be cut.We provide professional, comprehensive, on-site training for your staff at a fraction of the cost of off-site training programs.Learn a lot without spending a fortune. Copyright Harfst and Associates, inc. All rights reserved. Web Hosting by Yahoo! P.O. Box 276Crystal Lake, IL 60039ph: (815) 861-9082fax: (815) 477-7824wfh@mc.net





